### Remove duplicates from the dataframe and Save the cleaned dataframe back to a CSV file

Remove duplicates from the dataframe and Save the cleaned dataframe back to a CSV file¶

[7]:
import pandas as pd

# Load the CSV file
file_path = '/home/kaim/Documents/1000_richest_people_in_the_world.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)

# Remove duplicates from the dataframe
data_unique = data.drop_duplicates()

# Save the cleaned dataframe back to a CSV file
cleaned_file_path = '/home/kaim/Documents/1000_richest_people_in_the_world_cleaned.csv'
data_unique.to_csv(cleaned_file_path, index=False)

### Calculate the correlation matrix

Calculate the correlation matrix¶

[117]:
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the CSV file
file_path = '/home/kaim/Documents/1000_richest_people_in_the_world.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)

# Select only numerical columns
numerical_data = data.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64'])

# Calculate the correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = numerical_data.corr()

# Print the correlation matrix
print(correlation_matrix)



                         Net Worth (in billions)
Net Worth (in billions)                      1.0
## Distribution of Net Worth in Billions using Histogram

Distribution of Net Worth in Billions using Histogram¶

[34]:
# Histogram for Net Worth
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(data['Net Worth (in billions)'], bins=30, kde=True)
plt.title('Distribution of Net Worth in Billions')
plt.xlabel('Net Worth (in billions)')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.show()

## Evaluating average net worth by country and plotting a bat plot

Evaluating average net worth by country and plotting a bat plot¶

[56]:
# Average net worth by country
country_group = data.groupby('Country')['Net Worth (in billions)'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
print(country_group.head())

# Bar plot for average net worth by country
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 9))
country_group.plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Average Net Worth by Country')
plt.xlabel('Country')
plt.ylabel('Average Net Worth in Billions')
plt.show()

## Segment net worth by range and plot the segments using Bar plot

Segment net worth by range and plot the segments using Bar plot¶

[60]:
# Segment net worth by range
data['Net_Worth_Segment'] = pd.cut(data['Net Worth (in billions)'], bins=[0, 10, 50, 100, float('inf')], labels=['0-10', '10-50', '50-100', '100+'])

# Count of each segment
segment_counts = data['Net_Worth_Segment'].value_counts()
print(segment_counts)

# Bar plot for net worth segments
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
segment_counts.plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Net Worth Segments')
plt.xlabel('Net Worth Range (in Billions)')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.show()

Net_Worth_Segment
100+      512
50-100    259
10-50     188
0-10       41

## Cross-tabulation of industry by country using heatmap

Cross-tabulation of industry by country using heatmap¶

[78]:
# Cross-tabulation of industry by country
cross_tab = pd.crosstab(data['Country'], data['Industry'])
print(cross_tab)

# Heatmap of the cross-tabulation
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
sns.heatmap(cross_tab, annot=True, cmap='Blues')
plt.title('Cross-tabulation of Industry by Country')
plt.show()
